CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 17, 1959, pg. 3 reads: "Brown and Conlon Residences-...The modest home, right, of John W. (Jack) Conlon, 500 Mount Royal Blvd., Shaler Township, where Dr. Brown is said to have frequently visited. Mr. Conlon was named co-executor and the sole beneficiary in Dr. Brown's will. - Harris Photos."
TitMainTitle: Two story house owned by John W. (Jack) Conlon, with wood shingle siding, and front porch, at 500 Mount Royal Boulevard, Shaler Township
